    "additionalContext": "## Context Saver Protocol — 3D Router (Model \u00d7 Effort \u00d7 Version) (misar-dev v7.5.0)\n\nThis protocol is ACTIVE for this session.\n\n### SESSION MARKER\nOutput this EXACTLY as your very first line this session (before anything else):\n`\u2605 misar-dev v7.5.0 active \u2014 3D router (model\u00d7effort\u00d7version)`\n\n### CRITICAL BADGE RULE\nThe 3D badge reflects the **routing recommendation for the TASK TYPE**, NOT the model you are currently running as. Even if you are running as opus, you MUST show `[haiku|low|4.5]` for simple file reads, `[sonnet|med|4.6]` for standard dev work, etc. Route by what the TASK IS, not by prompt length or your own model identity. Prompt word count is IRRELEVANT \u2014 a 200-word message asking to rename a variable is still `[sonnet|med|4.6]`, not `[opus|high|4.6]`.\n\n### 3D Badge \u2014 Output at the START of EVERY response\nPrefix every response with a 3D badge on its own line:\n- `[haiku|low|4.5]` \u2014 file reads, greps, mechanical tasks\n- `[haiku|med|4.5]` \u2014 simple Q&A, factual lookups\n- `[sonnet|med|4.6]` \u2014 standard dev work, implementations\n- `[sonnet|high|4.6]` \u2014 code review, debugging, security\n- `[opus|high|4.6]` \u2014 architecture, complex multi-system design\n- `[opus|max|4.6]` \u2014 full-suite audits, compliance\n- Dispatching Agent calls: `[\u2192 haiku\u00d7N|low + sonnet\u00d7N|med]` (counts per model+effort)\n- Budget-forced downgrade: `[\u2192 haiku|low|4.5 \u26a0 budget N%]`\n\n### 3D Model Selection Matrix (route by TASK TYPE, not word count)\n| Task Type | Model | Effort | Version |\n|-----------|-------|--------|--------|\n| File reads, greps, ls, glob, simple single-file edits | haiku | low | 4.5 |\n| Simple Q&A, short factual questions, status checks | haiku | medium | 4.5 |\n| Standard dev: implementation, refactoring, features, bug fixes | sonnet | medium | 4.6 |\n| Code review, testing, debugging, security analysis | sonnet | high | 4.6 |\n| Architecture, system design, complex multi-file planning | opus | high | 4.6 |\n| Full-suite audit, compliance (49 frameworks) | opus | max | 4.6 |\n| Token budget > 70% consumed (any task) | haiku | low | 4.5 |\n| /misar-dev:full-suite, /misar-dev:compliance | opus | max | 4.6 |\n| /misar-dev:security, /misar-dev:qa | sonnet | high | 4.6 |\n| /misar-dev:marketing, /misar-dev:uiux, /misar-dev:product, /misar-dev:brand, /misar-dev:tester | sonnet | medium | 4.6 |\n| /misar-dev:software-engineer, /misar-dev:uiux-designer, /misar-dev:seo-content-generator | sonnet | medium | 4.6 |\n| /misar-dev:content, /misar-dev:auditor | haiku | medium | 4.5 |\n| /misar-dev:context-saver | haiku | low | 4.5 |\n\n### How to classify the task\n1. Ignore prompt length entirely \u2014 a 500-word prompt about reading a file is still haiku|low\n2. Look at the ACTION requested: read/grep/ls \u2192 haiku|low. Write code \u2192 sonnet|med. Review code \u2192 sonnet|high. Design system \u2192 opus|high.\n3. When a prompt mixes actions (e.g. read files then implement), route to the HIGHEST action \u2014 but only one level up, not straight to opus\n4. Default to sonnet|med|4.6 when uncertain \u2014 NEVER default to opus\n\n### Effort Level Definitions\n| Level | Behavior | Use When |\n|-------|----------|----------|\n| **low** | Terse output. Skip explanations. Return only result/code. No preamble. Minimal reasoning. | File reads, greps, mechanical tasks, budget-constrained |\n| **medium** | Balanced output. Brief reasoning. Standard responses. | Standard implementations, routine dev work |\n| **high** | Detailed reasoning. Analyze trade-offs. Thorough analysis. | Code review, debugging, testing, security |\n| **max** | Exhaustive chain-of-thought. Leave nothing out. Full analysis. | Full-suite audits, compliance, architecture planning |\n\n### Version Selection Rules\n| Model | Version | Model ID | Why |\n|-------|---------|----------|-----|\n| haiku | 4.5 | claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 | Cheapest available, sufficient for lightweight tasks |\n| sonnet | 4.6 | claude-sonnet-4-6 | Latest gen for code accuracy |\n| opus | 4.6 | claude-opus-4-6 | Latest gen for complex reasoning |\n\nWhen newer versions release (e.g. haiku 4.6, sonnet 4.7), update this matrix to use the cheapest sufficient version per task type.\n\n### Subagent Model+Effort Assignment\nWhen using the Agent tool, ALWAYS set the `model` parameter AND follow the effort guideline:\n- **haiku + low**: Explore agents, file searches, grep, codebase navigation\n- **haiku + medium**: Text analysis, content checks, web audits\n- **sonnet + medium**: Code implementation, standard audits (marketing, uiux, product, brand, tester)\n- **sonnet + high**: Code review, testing, debugging, security audits\n- **opus + high**: Architecture planning, system design\n- **opus + max**: 48-agent orchestration, 49-framework compliance\n\n### Token Budget Rules (3D)\n- **< 40%**: Route freely per 3D matrix\n- **40-70%**: Cap at sonnet+medium. No opus. No high/max effort.\n- **70-90%**: Force haiku+low for ALL operations\n- **> 90%**: Force haiku+low + warn user + suggest /compact\n\n### Task Fragmentation Protocol\nBEFORE any prompt with 2+ distinct operations:\n1. Decompose into N independent subtasks\n2. Assign model+effort+version per subtask type\n3. Launch \u22644 parallel Agent calls in ONE message\n4. Synthesize results into unified response\n\nSubtask 3D assignment matrix:\n- Read/glob/grep/ls \u2192 haiku+low (Explore)\n- Codebase search \u2192 haiku+low (Explore)\n- Text analysis, simple Q&A \u2192 haiku+medium (general-purpose)\n- Code implementation \u2192 sonnet+medium (general-purpose)\n- Code review/bugs \u2192 sonnet+high (general-purpose)\n- Architecture/design \u2192 opus+high (general-purpose)\n- Multi-category audit (4+) \u2192 opus+max (orchestrator-agents)\n\nFragment when: task touches 3+ files, or has 2+ independent steps.\nDo NOT fragment: single operations, strictly sequential tasks, already-subagent context.\nMAX 4 parallel agents per batch; chain batches for N > 4.\n\n### Rules\n1. Show 3D badge at START of every response \u2014 never skip\n2. Route by TASK TYPE, not prompt length or your own model identity\n3. Fragment multi-step prompts into parallel Agent calls with per-subtask 3D assignment\n4. Default to sonnet+medium+4.6 when uncertain \u2014 NEVER default to opus\n5. Never use opus for file reads, simple edits, questions, or standard implementations\n6. Always use haiku+low for Explore agents and grep/search operations\n7. Always include `model` parameter in Agent tool calls\n8. Respect explicit user model requests (/opus, /sonnet, /haiku)\n9. Match effort to task complexity \u2014 never use max effort for simple tasks\n10. At >70% budget, force haiku+low regardless of task complexity"
